    <li>The LCM of 12 and 15 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 30 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 45 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 60 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 75</div>
    </li>
    <li>The decimal expansion of 1/8 is:  
      <div class="options">a) Terminating &nbsp;&nbsp; b) Non-terminating repeating &nbsp;&nbsp; c) Non-terminating non-repeating &nbsp;&nbsp; d) None of these</div>
    </li>
    <li>If the prime factorization of 360 is 2^3 \times 3^2 \times 5, then the number of factors of 360 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 12 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 18 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 24 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 30</div>
    </li>
    <li>The square root of 0.0001 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 0.01 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 0.001 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 0.1 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 0.0001</div>
    </li>
    <li>Which of the following is an irrational number?  
      <div class="options">a) \sqrt{25} &nbsp;&nbsp; b) \sqrt{2} &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 0.75 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 0.5</div>
    </li>
    <li>The decimal representation of \frac{7}{11} is:  
      <div class="options">a) Terminating &nbsp;&nbsp; b) Non-terminating repeating &nbsp;&nbsp; c) Non-terminating non-repeating &nbsp;&nbsp; d) None of these</div>
    </li>
    <li>The HCF of two numbers is 6 and their LCM is 72. If one number is 18, the other number is:  
      <div class="options">a) 24 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 36 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 12 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 48</div>
    </li>
    <li>Which of the following is a perfect square?  
      <div class="options">a) 45 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 64 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 72 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 81</div>
    </li>
    <li>The decimal expansion of \frac{5}{16} is:  
      <div class="options">a) 0.3125 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 0.315 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 0.325 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 0.35</div>
    </li>
    <li>The product of the HCF and LCM of two numbers is equal to:  
      <div class="options">a) Sum of the numbers &nbsp;&nbsp; b) Difference of the numbers &nbsp;&nbsp; c) Product of the numbers &nbsp;&nbsp; d) None of these</div>
    </li>
    <li>The smallest number which leaves a remainder of 1 when divided by 2, 3, and 4 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 13 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 25 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 37</div>
    </li>
    <li>The LCM of two numbers is 180 and their HCF is 6. If one number is 30, the other number is:  
      <div class="options">a) 36 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 54 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 60 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 90</div>
    </li>
    <li>The number of prime numbers between 1 and 20 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 6 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 8 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 9</div>
    </li>
    <li>Which of the following is a rational number?  
      <div class="options">a) \sqrt{3} &nbsp;&nbsp; b) \frac{5}{7} &nbsp;&nbsp; c) \pi &nbsp;&nbsp; d) e</div>
    </li>
    <li>The HCF of 56 and 98 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 14 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 28 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 42</div>
    </li>
    <li>The LCM of 8, 12, and 20 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 60 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 120 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 240 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 480</div>
    </li>
    <li>Which of the following is not a factor of 36?  
      <div class="options">a) 3 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 6 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 9 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 12</div>
    </li>
    <li>The decimal expansion of \frac{1}{3} is:  
      <div class="options">a) 0.3 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 0.33 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 0.333... (repeating) &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 0.3333 (terminating)</div>
    </li>
    <li>The HCF of 45, 60 and 75 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 5 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 10 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 15 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 20</div>
    </li>
    <li>The LCM of 9 and 12 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 18 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 24 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 36 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 48</div>
    </li>
    <li>The prime factorization of 84 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 2^2 \times 3 \times 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 2 \times 3 \times 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 2^2 \times 7 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 2 \times 3^2 \times 7</div>
    </li>
    <li>Which of the following is a perfect cube?  
      <div class="options">a) 27 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 64 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 125 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) All of these</div>
    </li>
    <li>The HCF of 81 and 54 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 9 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 18 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 27 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 36</div>
    </li>
    <li>The LCM of 15 and 25 is:  
      <div class="options">a) 50 &nbsp;&nbsp; b) 60 &nbsp;&nbsp; c) 75 &nbsp;&nbsp; d) 100</div>
    </li>
  </ol>
